									<p>The working procedure of a deodorant filling machine is a systematic, step-by-step process designed to ensure precision, efficiency, and product safety. It is tailored to handle different deodorant types—stick pastes, roll-on liquids, and spray solutions—while adhering to room-temperature filling and piston metering principles. Below is the detailed, standardized operation workflow:</p>								</div>
