									<p class="elementor-icon-box-description">
						The filled molds travel along a cooling tunnel for cooling the liquid into solid.The liquid fastly solidifies from the outside in. The cooling rate is precisely controlled; cooling too quickly can cause stress and cracking, while cooling too slowly is inefficient.					</p>
				
